    "concentration": false,
    "desc": "You speak a one-word command to a creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or follow the command on its next turn. Choose the command from these options: • Approach: The target moves toward you by the shortest and most direct route, ending its turn if it moves within 5 feet of you. • Drop: The target drops whatever it is holding and then ends its turn. • Flee: The target spends its turn moving away from you by the fastest available means. • Grovel: The target has the Prone condition and then ends its turn. • Halt: On its turn, the target doesn't move and takes no action or Bonus Action.",
    "higherLevel": "You can affect one additional creature for each spell slot level above 1.",
